        "timestamp": 1506878078
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We just deployed here a major significant refactoring of how emoji reactions work in Zulip (with a new backend API, etc.; the old one still exists for mobile compatibility though).  This refactoring should allow us to solve several problems that were previously intractable (e.g. things having to do with deactivated realm emoji).  I'd love it if a few people played around with emoji reactions trying to find something broken (there's 3 major cases: <img alt=\":zulip:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"/static/generated/emoji/images/emoji/unicode/zulip.png\" title=\"zulip\">, realm emoji like <img alt=\":jenkins:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"/user_avatars/2/emoji/jenkins.png\" title=\"jenkins\">, and normal emoji).</p>",
        "id": 329408,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1510940853
    },
